{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold a \"cumulative\" second Brexit referendum; votes added to the first result",
        "additional_details": "People who argue that a second referendum would be against democratic principles ought to be comfortable with this idea, as the \"pro-Brexit\" campaign would effectively start with an advantage; and the \"anti-Brexit\" campaign would effectively start behind the start line.  This is the most equitable approach to solving the current views against holding a second referendum.",
        "background": "The main objection to holding a second referendum on Brexit is that it would not respect the result of the first referendum.  There is an easy solution to this.  Hold a cumulative second referendum, whereby the result and number of votes would be simply added to the result of the first",
